    • Field Detail

      • PORTRAIT_IMAGE_NAME

        public static final java.lang.String PORTRAIT_IMAGE_NAME
        Name of the image sent to MetadataListener that contains portrait image. This image will be sent to MetadataListener during recognition process if displaying of face image is enabled (see setDisplayFaceImage(boolean), and receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED image is enabled with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)

      • FULL_DOCUMENT_IMAGE_NAME

        public static final java.lang.String FULL_DOCUMENT_IMAGE_NAME
        Name of the image sent to MetadataListener that contains full document. This image will be sent to MetadataListener during recognition process if displaying of full document image is enabled (see setDisplayFullDocumentImage(boolean), and receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED image is enabled with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)

      • SIGNATURE_IMAGE_NAME

        public static final java.lang.String SIGNATURE_IMAGE_NAME
        Name of the image sent to MetadataListener that contains signature. This image will be sent to MetadataListener during recognition process if displaying of signature image is enabled (see setDisplaySignatureImage(boolean), and receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED image is enabled with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)

      • setDisplayFaceImage

        public void setDisplayFaceImage(boolean displayFaceImage)
        Sets whether face image from ID card should be sent to MetadataListener. If enabled, image will be of type ImageType.DEWARPED, and the name of the image (see Image.getImageName()) will be equal to #FACE_IMAGE_NAME, so make sure you subscribe to receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED images with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)
        Parameters:
        displayFaceImage - whether face image should be sent to MetadataListener.
